Step1:
Create a Lambda Function : MyWebSiteLambda
Runtime : Python 3.6
Role : Create a New Role - MyLambdaExecutionRole
Policy Templates : Search for "MicroServices"
Create Lambda Function

Step2:
Copy the content of helloawsguys.py into the code editor
Click File, Save and Deploy button

Step3:
Click on Add Trigger
Select API Gateway
Create an API
API type - REST API
Security - IAM
Click on Add
Click on Deploy

Step4:
Verify the APIGateway, which will open the API Gateway
Delete the Any Method


Step 5:
CReate a Method - GET 
Integration type - Lambda Function
Use Lambda Proxy Integration - checked
Find your lambda function

Step 6:
Deploy the API
Choose default 

Step 7:
Copy the Invoke URL from GET
Go to index.html and replace that api gateway url with your apigateway url .. which is in 11th line

Step 8:
Create s3 bucket
Put the index and error.html 
enable static website hosting
update the proper s3 permissions
Verify the s3 static endpoint is working or not.

Explain about few things on developers tools

